## USER RESEARCH (Top 5 Pain Points)

**1. Length Anxiety - "Are My Nails Even Long Enough?"**  
Biggest concern: *"Can I actually achieve almond if my nails are short?"* Users constantly ask about minimum length requirements. Need reality check: requires nails extending *"slightly past fingertip"* (2-3mm minimum) - anything shorter becomes stubby/weird. Also: hyponychium concerns (nail bed extends past fingertip for some people, making *"short"* relative).

**2. Shape Definition Confusion - "Is This Almond or Just Oval?"**  
Users struggle to differentiate short almond from short oval since taper is less dramatic at shorter lengths. Common frustration: *"I filed it almond but it looks oval."* Need: side-by-side comparison showing the subtle difference (short almond has more pronounced taper at tip, oval is more uniformly curved).

**3. Design Limitations - "What Actually Works on This Small Canvas?"**  
Reality check needed: intricate nail art that looks amazing on long almonds can look cramped/messy on short versions. Users want to know: which designs translate well vs which need more length. Frustration with Pinterest showing elaborate art that *"only works on long nails."*

**4. Filing Symmetry Challenges - "One Side Always Ends Up Shorter"**  
Short nails = less room for error when filing taper. Users report filing too much off one side, creating uneven shape. Common issue: *"I keep trying to fix it and making it worse."* Need: filing technique that prevents over-correction (file slowly, alternate sides frequently, use center-mark guide).

**5. Professional Appropriateness Questions - "Will These Work for My Office?"**  
Many users choosing short almond BECAUSE they need work-appropriate length but still want elegance. Questions: *"Are these too edgy for corporate?"* *"Will my boss think they're unprofessional?"* Need reassurance: short almond is office-friendly, less dramatic than stiletto/long versions.

**User Sentiment:** Practical optimism. They WANT elegant almond look but need it to fit real life (work, typing, daily tasks). Not chasing Instagram perfection - seeking beautiful + functional. Slightly insecure about whether their natural nail length can pull off the shape.

